==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|striven||to strive|lang=enm}} from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|estriver||to compete, quarrel|lang=fro}} from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|estrif||quarrel, dispute|lang=fro}}, alteration (influenced by {{etyl|gem|en}} forms related to {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*strīban||to strive}}, compare {{etyl|dum|-}} {{term|streven||to strive|lang=dum}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|streben||to strive|lang=de}}) of {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|estrit|||lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*strīd||quarrel, dispute}} from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*strīdō||combat, strife}}. Akin to {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|strīt||quarrel|lang=goh}} ({{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Streit|||lang=de}}), {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|strītan||to fight|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|strið|strīð|strife, contention|lang=non}}. More at [[stride]].

